+{"id":"bd-0kmi1","title":"Reject e2compr clusters whose holemap cannot consume decompressed bytes","description":"Fresh-eyes follow-up around ext4 e2compr: after checksum verification and codec decode, decompress_e2compr_cluster unpacks the decompressed payload through the cluster holemap but never verifies that every decoded byte was consumed. A structurally inconsistent cluster can mark too many blocks as holes and silently discard checksum-valid payload bytes, returning zero-filled data instead of reporting corruption. Acceptance: factor/guard holemap expansion so leftover decoded bytes are rejected with FfsError::Corruption; add focused valid and inconsistent-holemap tests; update spec/parity docs if wording mentions e2compr integrity; run targeted e2compr tests plus fmt/diff/UBS/workspace check/clippy.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"cod-fs","created_at":"2026-04-27T06:16:47.049712795Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-27T06:22:15.091101437Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T06:22:15.088576777Z","close_reason":"Rejected e2compr clusters whose holemap cannot consume every decoded byte, added focused valid/inconsistent-holemap tests, and updated spec/parity docs.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
