 {"id":"bd-0sxk9","title":"CONFORMANCE: ext4 ext4_inode on-disk golden round-trip harness","description":"# Family B (shipped 2026-04-24, closed in place)

Freezes the `ext4_inode` layout via 10 golden-fixture tests in `crates/ffs-inode/tests/conformance_inode_golden.rs`:

- 128-byte regfile: bit-exact round-trip + field-by-field assertions.
- 256-byte directory with extended area (extra_isize=0x20, nsec timestamps, crtime).
- 256-byte inode with split uid/gid (both halves populated — regression guard for u16-truncation bugs).
- 5-GiB size round-trip (size_hi split at offset 0x6C).
- Short-payload rejection (< 128 bytes).
- extra_isize-past-boundary rejection.
- 60-byte i_block region preserved verbatim.

Uses `ffs_inode::fuzz_serialize_inode` (doc-hidden public wrapper for `serialize_inode`) and `Ext4Inode::parse_from_bytes`.

Run: `rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch_target_ffs_inode_cc_conformance cargo test -p ffs-inode --test conformance_inode_golden`.

Divergences at `crates/ffs-inode/tests/DISCREPANCIES.md` (3 ACCEPTED: checksum field zeroed by serializer, 128-byte inodes have no extended area, no encoder yet for DirEntry/Superblock/GroupDesc — out of scope for this family).","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-24T22:34:10.321008Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-24T22:34:10.321008Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T22:34:10.321008Z","close_reason":"10 tests green via rch; fixtures inlined, DISCREPANCIES.md documented","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
